abstract: A look around the nation at the best in college football from Week 7.
snippet: A look around the nation at the best in college football from Week 7.
lead_paragraph: RYAN TANNEHILL AND ROBERT GRIFFIN III The opposing quarterbacks in No. 21 Texas A&M's 55-28 victory at home against No. 20 Baylor combined for 845 passing yards and 9 touchdown passes. The Aggies' Tannehill, left, threw for 415 yards and a career-high 6 scores, and Griffin, right, had a team-record 430 yards and 3 touchdowns.

headline.main: The Day's Best in College Football
